I've wanted to fly since I was little.
And I did it today… today, I flew a plane. I'm still having trouble realizing.
flightaware data.
I'm going to try to go again on Saturday. The weather is not terrible right now, but it's only Monday.
The difficulties are already starting to appear. I'll probably have a LOT of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it will take an ENORMOUS amount of time and require a LOT of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to solve and, for now, it seems *totally* surmountable. It's just that it will require a lot of time and $$.
In case the challenge that awaits me interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. It doesn't issue a medical certificate if you're following treatment for it.
https://youtu.be/W5JSfq6LLAU?si=xIxPaY8ayqqNSj4c
